00:19:51,070 --> 00:19:51,880
I always paid close attention

284
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:53,830
to their first words

285
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:58,020
because they reveal the most genuine

286
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:01,350
and immediate reactions
of the interrogated.

287
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:06,400
But now I'm sitting here.

288
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,310
I find myself unsure

289
00:20:09,310 --> 00:20:10,970
what my first words should be.

290
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:16,790
So,

291
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:20,750
you were thinking carefully what your
first words should be

292
00:20:20,910 --> 00:20:23,050
and your silence was part of your tactics.

293
00:20:23,050 --> 00:20:24,550
I am both the maze itself

294
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,850
and its entrance.

295
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:30,950
It's like playing chess against myself

296
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:34,320
and I don't know which move to make.

297
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:37,920
I don't know

298
00:20:39,030 --> 00:20:40,560
if you can understand this.

299
00:20:41,030 --> 00:20:41,720
I can.

300
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:45,840
You opened the entrance to the maze
for others,

301
00:20:45,940 --> 00:20:47,870
and found an exit for yourself,

302
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:50,030
which is justifiable defense.

303
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,660
With my years of experience as a prosecutor,

304
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:55,990
what I did was entirely justifiable defense.

305
00:21:04,110 --> 00:21:04,960
It seems

306
00:21:06,270 --> 00:21:07,480
you've replayed the scene

307
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:09,410
of the case in your mind many times.

308
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:12,100
If I were the prosecutor for this case,

309
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:13,360
I absolutely wouldn't

310
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:15,920
charge myself with excessive defense.

311
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,850
Because I know that way,

312
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:20,310
my actions would still be ruled
as justifiable defense.

313
00:21:20,310 --> 00:21:22,310
Have you figured out everything then?

314
00:21:22,310 --> 00:21:23,510
Who kidnapped you?

315
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:28,080
I haven't figured it out yet.

316
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:30,120
Let me give you a hint.

317
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:32,430
14 years ago,

318
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:34,480
the Case 6.28 at the library.

319
00:21:34,830 --> 00:21:36,160
You were in charge of it.

320
00:21:36,930 --> 00:21:39,270
Some people believed it was
justifiable defense.

321
00:21:39,270 --> 00:21:42,200
But you still initiated a public prosecution
for it.

322
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:45,420
The deceased was Zhou Lin.

323
00:21:46,270 --> 00:21:47,790
The suspect was Li Mufeng.

324
00:21:48,770 --> 00:21:50,160
But I don't remember

325
00:21:50,650 --> 00:21:52,090
anyone in that case

326
00:21:52,690 --> 00:21:54,890
whose age matches that of my kidnapper.

327
00:21:58,380 --> 00:22:00,250
Zhou Lin's father, Zhou Delong.

328
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:03,960
I see.

329
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,600
Back then, I only met Zhou Lin's mother.

330
00:22:09,410 --> 00:22:10,760
I only found out later

331
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:14,030
that his parents had divorced long ago.

332
00:22:14,470 --> 00:22:15,590
Duan Hongshan.

333
00:22:15,830 --> 00:22:17,440
You killed Zhou Delong.

334
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:19,550
That may be considered as justifiable defense.

335
00:22:19,550 --> 00:22:21,400
It could also be intentional homicide

336
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:23,350
disguised as justifiable defense.

337
00:22:23,350 --> 00:22:24,030
This

338
00:22:24,420 --> 00:22:26,350
is the reality you should face now.

339
00:22:27,070 --> 00:22:28,720
It's very clear now

340
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:34,010
that it was Zhou Delong

341
00:22:34,590 --> 00:22:36,590
who orchestrated this kidnapping.

342
00:22:38,590 --> 00:22:40,000
If he had killed me,

343
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:42,880
he would have destroyed my present.

344
00:22:43,930 --> 00:22:45,350
If he was killed by me,

345
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:48,240
it would have destroyed my past.

346
00:22:53,310 --> 00:22:55,100
So you need to think carefully.

347
00:22:56,450 --> 00:22:58,370
The Case 6.28 from 14 years ago

348
00:22:59,450 --> 00:23:00,580
is a chance.

349
00:23:01,950 --> 00:23:04,080
Zhou Delong wanted to take this chance

350
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:05,920
to make people challenge

351
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:08,350
all my previously settled cases

352
00:23:09,020 --> 00:23:10,640
so as to ruin my reputation

353
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:12,340
and thereby undermine

354
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:14,920
the public trust in the justice system.

355
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:25,880
Yingying.

356
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:27,590
Jing.

357
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:29,880
Did you work out that math problem yesterday?

358
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:30,810
I chose it.
Jing.

359
00:23:32,270 --> 00:23:33,960
I've been looking for you. We're late.
Come quickly.

360
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:34,590
What's the hurry?

361
00:23:34,590 --> 00:23:36,110
Be careful to choose the person you chat with.

362
00:23:36,110 --> 00:23:37,040
Hurry to school.

363
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:15,880
Dad.

364
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,310
Are you there?

365
00:24:22,790 --> 00:24:23,680
Yingying.

366
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,520
What's wrong?

367
00:24:47,070 --> 00:24:48,680
You look so pale.

368
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:49,550
I'm fine.

369
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,720
Do you need me to ask a teacher here?

370
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:53,440
No need, thanks.

371
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:55,160
Let's go, hurry up.

372
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,680
Don't you know who she is?

373
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,540
She's Duan Yingying from Class 5.

374
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,360
Her father is that...

375
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,550
Yes, her father is that

376
00:25:03,550 --> 00:25:05,440
prosecutor who committed a murder.

377
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:06,440
Really? Let's leave.

378
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,240
Hurry, hurry!

379
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:34,420
[People's Procuratorate in Yuyan District, Wuyan City]
[Detention Center]

380
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:37,600
Do you remember Zhou?

381
00:25:38,070 --> 00:25:39,800
Wasn't he released last month?

382
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,000
I heard

383
00:25:41,310 --> 00:25:42,830
he has a daughter in college

384
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:44,750
who was bullied by classmates

385
00:25:44,830 --> 00:25:45,750
and had to drop out.

386
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:46,720
Really?

387
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:48,720
It's true. Why would I lie to you?

388
00:25:49,070 --> 00:25:51,000
My cousin is his neighbor.

389
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,110
He told me about it

390
00:25:52,110 --> 00:25:53,910
when he visited me this morning.

391
00:25:54,550 --> 00:25:55,830
That's just his fate.

392
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,200
That's right.

393
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:00,070
It's all because he was once in prison.

394
00:26:00,070 --> 00:26:00,510
Right?

395
00:26:00,510 --> 00:26:01,370
Duan Hongshan.

396
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:02,350
Here.

397
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:04,520
Your lawyer wants to see you.

398
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,200
In your case,

399
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,160
there is neither physical evidence

400
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:15,550
nor eyewitnesses.

401
00:26:16,310 --> 00:26:18,550
The injuries and marks on your body

402
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:20,440
only prove you were kidnapped,

403
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:22,400
but can't prove your life

404
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:24,030
was at stake at that time.

405
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:27,320
This case isn't that simple.

406
00:26:30,030 --> 00:26:31,270
Many people online are saying

407
00:26:31,270 --> 00:26:32,150
that as a prosecutor,

408
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:34,590
you should be severely punished for
breaking the law.

409
00:26:34,590 --> 00:26:35,390
Fortunately,

410
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:37,030
many others believe

411
00:26:37,030 --> 00:26:39,030
your actions were justifiable defense.

412
00:26:39,030 --> 00:26:39,720
The key is to

413
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:42,000
gain the upper hand before the procuratorate decides

414
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,560
whether to approve your arrest.

415
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:44,850
Your case is special,

416
00:26:44,880 --> 00:26:46,210
and so is your identity.

417
00:26:46,310 --> 00:26:48,030
So the procuratorate might conduct

418
00:26:48,030 --> 00:26:49,750
a very thorough investigation into it.

419
00:26:49,750 --> 00:26:50,880
Based on your account,

420
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:52,070
I also believe your actions

421
00:26:52,070 --> 00:26:53,530
are justifiable defense.

422
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:56,100
You just need to tell the truth, understand?

423
00:26:57,830 --> 00:26:59,350
You don't understand what I meant.

424
00:26:59,350 --> 00:27:00,270
I do.

425
00:27:01,310 --> 00:27:02,070
Just sign it.

426
00:27:07,550 --> 00:27:09,260
Why is there another document?

427
00:27:09,260 --> 00:27:09,550
[Real Estate Transfer Agreement]

428
00:27:09,550 --> 00:27:12,030
The other one is about the right to transfer
your real estate.

429
00:27:12,030 --> 00:27:13,270
I've changed the visitation schedule

430
00:27:13,270 --> 00:27:15,200
on the custody transfer document.

431
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:17,510
You can see your daughter once a week.

432
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:19,590
What for?

433
00:27:24,310 --> 00:27:26,310
I'm not the way I was when I was young.

434
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:28,650
Now I always prepare a backup plan.

435
00:27:33,070 --> 00:27:34,930
My apartment is old and run-down.

436
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:36,610
It's not worth much.

437
00:27:37,350 --> 00:27:39,010
Whatever is left to Yingying,

438
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:41,750
I'll take it all.

439
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:03,920
Are you sure

440
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:06,480
that you'll win?

441
00:28:09,510 --> 00:28:10,750
If you're not so confident,

442
00:28:10,750 --> 00:28:13,280
there's still time for you to get a new lawyer.

443
00:28:13,550 --> 00:28:15,270
Do you know who kidnapped me?

444
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:23,110
I don't care who he is.

445
00:28:23,750 --> 00:28:25,750
Based on the distance from your home to
the crime scene,

446
00:28:25,750 --> 00:28:27,790
I can determine this wasn't a coincidence,

447
00:28:27,790 --> 00:28:29,850
but a carefully planned kidnapping.

448
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:30,750
Why

449
00:28:30,750 --> 00:28:32,640
did the person kidnap you?

450
00:28:32,750 --> 00:28:34,030
When he was doing it, he must have known

451
00:28:34,030 --> 00:28:36,200
it would end with either you or him dead.

452
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:37,130
What was he up to?

453
00:28:45,550 --> 00:28:46,550
It's Zhou Delong,

454
00:28:49,790 --> 00:28:50,920
Zhou Lin's father.

455
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,920
Sign the agreement after you're released.

456
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:15,450
I suppose you agree with me.

457
00:29:20,750 --> 00:29:21,790
For this case,

458
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:24,940
I won't charge you.

459
00:29:47,380 --> 00:29:52,750
[Trial Calling]

460
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,330
Do you have a moment?

461
00:30:13,590 --> 00:30:14,640
If you're free,

462
00:30:15,590 --> 00:30:16,850
I'd like to talk to you.

463
00:30:20,550 --> 00:30:21,110
Sure.

464
00:30:24,960 --> 00:30:26,200
Fourteen years ago,

465
00:30:27,110 --> 00:30:29,770
Duan Hongshan and I handled your case together.

466
00:30:30,110 --> 00:30:31,510
After all these years,

467
00:30:32,240 --> 00:30:33,480
there's a question

468
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,060
I've always wanted to ask you.

469
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,350
Go ahead, ask.

470
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,170
Have you ever hated Duan Hongshan?

471
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:52,880
Well,

472
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:56,680
if it hadn't been for Director Duan,

473
00:30:57,240 --> 00:30:59,570
I might have ended up in a worse situation.

474
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:04,350
I know that.

475
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:05,960
After you were released,

476
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:08,680
Duan Hongshan always tried his best to help you.

477
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:10,830
Do you think

478
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:14,350
Zhou Lin's family hated Duan Hongshan?

479
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:18,640
Well...

480
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:22,160
I'm not really sure about that.

481
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:23,720
My opinion doesn't matter anyway.

482
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,350
It does

483
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:26,310
because the person who kidnapped Duan Hongshan

484
00:31:26,310 --> 00:31:28,310
and was killed by him in defense

485
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:31,240
was Zhou Lin's father, Zhou Delong.

486
00:31:32,830 --> 00:31:34,400
But this is so strange.

487
00:31:35,270 --> 00:31:37,440
His father should have hated you more.

488
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,760
Why did he kidnap Duan Hongshan?

489
00:31:40,070 --> 00:31:41,920
Now he lost his life.

490
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:44,750
It just doesn't make sense.

491
00:31:45,830 --> 00:31:47,160
He definitely hated me.

492
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:48,590
After I got out,

493
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:51,070
he threatened me.

494
00:31:51,750 --> 00:31:52,810
He threatened you?

495
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:55,720
Where? When?

496
00:31:56,270 --> 00:31:57,960
Did he mention Duan Hongshan?

497
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:06,990
You don't need to tell me.

498
00:32:07,350 --> 00:32:09,550
I'm Duan Hongshan's lawyer now.

499
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,960
You can tell what you know

500
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,000
to the investigators.

501
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,240
Maybe

502
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:23,760
it could help Duan Hongshan.

503
00:32:30,750 --> 00:32:32,350
I shouldn't bother you more.

504
00:32:41,070 --> 00:32:43,400
[Fragile items]

505
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:44,960
You can think about it.

506
00:32:47,250 --> 00:32:48,520
[Fragile items]

507
00:33:16,750 --> 00:33:18,640
Everyone, please stop for a moment.

508
00:33:18,640 --> 00:33:19,830
Please come here.

509
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:22,680
The police officers are here

510
00:33:22,680 --> 00:33:24,480
and they need your cooperation.

511
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:27,160
Here is the thing.

512
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:29,550
We're searching underwater at the East Suburb Fishery

513
00:33:29,550 --> 00:33:30,950
for important evidence.

514
00:33:31,270 --> 00:33:33,830
But we don't have many good divers at our bureau

515
00:33:33,830 --> 00:33:36,030
and the underwater conditions are quite complicated.

516
00:33:36,030 --> 00:33:36,750
So,

517
00:33:36,750 --> 00:33:37,920
we need you

518
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,440
to help us with it.

519
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:41,460
Don't worry, officer.

520
00:33:41,550 --> 00:33:42,160
They

521
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:43,830
are the best divers here.

522
00:33:43,830 --> 00:33:45,030
They'll do a good job.

523
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:47,680
Well, officer,

524
00:33:48,030 --> 00:33:49,880
it's been raining non-stop for days.

525
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:51,350
If we go into the water now,

526
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:53,480
wouldn't it be too dangerous?

527
00:33:54,270 --> 00:33:55,030
Let me do it.

528
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:05,440
First,

529
00:34:06,270 --> 00:34:08,400
ensure your own safety.

530
00:34:08,630 --> 00:34:10,280
The weather is quite bad,

531
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:12,480
so make sure to search thoroughly.

532
00:34:12,550 --> 00:34:13,960
Pay special attention to

533
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:15,510
any phones,

534
00:34:15,670 --> 00:34:17,630
keys, knives,

535
00:34:17,630 --> 00:34:20,150
and all other suspicious items.

536
00:34:20,150 --> 00:34:21,360
Find them all.

537
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:54,030
Miss.

538
00:34:55,110 --> 00:34:56,590
Have you found anything?

539
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:57,590
No.

540
00:35:32,190 --> 00:35:32,800
Meal time.

541
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:39,640
This is male detention cell 103,

542
00:35:40,110 --> 00:35:42,030
currently holding 10 inmates.

543
00:35:42,880 --> 00:35:44,230
Everyone, stand up!

544
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:47,740
Turn left, and turn right.

545
00:35:58,070 --> 00:35:59,590
How's the food?

546
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:01,510
Any issues you need to report?

547
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:03,230
Report, sir! None.

548
00:36:04,230 --> 00:36:05,150
Have you experienced

549
00:36:05,150 --> 00:36:06,800
any unfair treatment?

550
00:36:07,260 --> 00:36:08,480
Report, sir! No.

551
00:36:13,070 --> 00:36:14,030
Sit down and eat.

552
00:36:32,710 --> 00:36:34,880
I went to the detention center this morning

553
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:35,880
and ran into Duan.

554
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:37,150
Duan?

555
00:36:38,110 --> 00:36:39,070
How is he doing?

556
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:44,480
Just like any other suspect who's just been locked up.

557
00:36:46,190 --> 00:36:47,360
In that place,

558
00:36:47,840 --> 00:36:49,030
no one can look good.

559
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,400
But Duan

560
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:54,280
has been a prosecutor for 20 years,

561
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:57,740
and he's the Director of the First Procuratorial Department.

562
00:36:57,760 --> 00:36:58,710
Do you remember

563
00:36:59,280 --> 00:37:00,070
in the year

564
00:37:00,230 --> 00:37:02,490
when the TV station came to interview us,

565
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:03,800
he said

566
00:37:04,320 --> 00:37:05,510
every prosecutor,

567
00:37:05,510 --> 00:37:07,110
no matter what situation they face,

568
00:37:07,110 --> 00:37:09,320
must remain calm, rational, and objective

569
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:12,070
